| Connectors, Jumpers, Wiring | -                         | Internal connections                     |

---

### 3.2 Connection Details

* **Motor System:**
  The ESP32-S3-BOX-3B connects to the TB6612 motor driver via GPIO pins, which in turn drives four N20 DC geared motors. Motor power is supplied from the 12V Li-ion battery. The schematic shows all A/B control lines and encoder connections if present.

* **Obstacle and Cliff Sensors:**

  * **HC-SR04 Ultrasonic Sensor**: Connected to ESP32 GPIO pins (Trig and Echo), used for obstacle avoidance.
  * **TCRT5000 Infrared Sensor**: Connected to digital input pins of ESP32, providing real-time cliff/edge detection to prevent falling.

* **Environmental Sensing:**

  * **DHT11 sensor** is connected to GPIO pins for temperature and humidity data collection, reported to the user via the interface.

* **Audio & Display:**

  * The onboard microphone and speaker of ESP32-S3-BOX-3B handle voice command input/output. The built-in touch display can be used for information feedback or status indicators.

* **Power System:**

  * The 12V 2550mAh lithium battery is the main power source, supplying motors and the controller via regulated power lines (5V/3.3V LDO conversion will be in Motor Driver D24A for logic and sensors).

* **Buttons:**

  * Onboard BOOT/RESET buttons for entering bootloader mode and resetting the device during programming or troubleshooting.

---

### 3.4 Role of Each Hardware Module

* **ESP32-S3-BOX-3B:**
  The brain of the robot; responsible for sensor data processing, motor control, local speech recognition, and cloud AI connectivity. Handles all high-level logic and user interaction.

* **TB6612 Motor Driver & N20 Motors:**
  Executes motion commands; enables differential drive and complex movement patterns for the robot (forward, backward, turning, exploration, etc.).

* **HC-SR04 Ultrasonic Sensor:**
  Provides real-time obstacle detection to ensure safe navigation and automatic stopping if an object is too close.

* **TCRT5000 Infrared Sensor:**
  Detects the absence of ground (“cliff”), automatically stopping the robot and preventing accidental falls.

* **DHT11 Sensor:**
  Reports environmental temperature and humidity, adding an IoT element for smart sensing and context awareness.

* **12V 2550mAh Li-ion Battery:**
  Ensures the robot can operate for an extended period with sufficient power for all motors and logic circuits.

* **Power Regulation Module:**
  Steps down voltage as needed for sensors, logic, and controller, ensuring stable operation.

* **Mic/Speaker/Touchscreen:**
  Enables multi-modal user interaction through voice commands, spoken responses, and touch-based control or status display.

