## 4. Software Implementation

### 4.1 Project Structure

```plaintext
/project-root/
├── main/
│   ├── app_main.c           # Main application logic, entry point
│   ├── motor_control.c/h    # Motor driver abstraction and movement control
│   ├── voice_module.c/h     # Wake word, command recognition, voice I/O
│   ├── ai_module.c/h        # GPT API requests and response handling
│   ├── sensor_module.c/h    # Obstacle, cliff, and environment sensors
│   ├── utils.c/h            # Utility functions, configuration, error handling
│   └── ...
├── components/              # Third-party or custom reusable modules
├── sdkconfig                # ESP-IDF config file
├── Makefile / CMakeLists.txt
└── README.mkd
```

* **main/app\_main.c**: Initializes hardware, runs main control loop, dispatches events.
* **main/motor\_control.c**: Provides movement primitives (forward, backward, stop, turn) and integrates with safety logic.
* **main/voice\_module.c**: Handles voice activation (WakeNet), local command recognition (MultiNet), audio I/O.
* **main/ai\_module.c**: Communicates with OpenAI API, processes natural language input, formats response.
* **main/sensor\_module.c**: Reads and filters data from ultrasonic, infrared, and DHT11 sensors, triggers events on hazard.
* **main/utils.c**: Common helper routines, logging, error reporting, timing.

