## 7. Testing

### 7.1 Test Approach

* **Manual functional testing**: Each feature (motion, obstacle avoidance, voice control, AI chat, sensor reading) was validated by direct operation and observation.
* **Scenario testing**: Combined use-cases, such as walking while obstacles or cliffs appear, stress testing under low battery, multiple voice commands in sequence.
* **Sensor simulation**: Used controlled objects and surfaces to trigger obstacle and cliff sensors at various distances/angles.
* **Speech accuracy testing**: Recorded command words at different volumes, accents, and environmental noise.

---

### 7.2 Example Test Cases & Results

| Test Case                    | Expected Result                      | Actual Result              | Pass/Fail |
| ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------ | -------------------------- | --------- |
| Move forward, no obstacles   | Robot drives straight                | Drives straight            | Pass      |
| Obstacle at 7cm              | Stops before collision               | Stops at \~7.5cm           | Pass      |
| Cliff detected (table edge)  | Halts immediately                    | Halts within 1cm           | Pass      |
| "move forward" voice command | Robot moves                          | Responds & moves           | Pass      |
| "walk around" (explore mode) | Random safe movement, avoids hazards | Roams, avoids edges/blocks | Pass      |
| Ambient noise voice test     | No false activation                  | No false activation        | Pass      |
| DHT11 reports temp/humidity  | Data appears on screen               | As expected                | Pass      |

---

### 7.3 Bug List & Reliability Improvement

* **Issue**: Ultrasonic sometimes missed very thin objects.
  **Fix**: Added IR sensor cross-check; increased polling rate.
* **Issue**: Early build occasionally stalled after long cloud response time.
  **Fix**: Added timeout and fallback to local command set.
* **Issue**: Cliff detection jitter.
  **Fix**: Software debounce on IR sensor readings.
* **Reliability**:
  All core safety systems (obstacle, cliff) operate entirely on-device, ensuring continued safety even with network loss or high cloud latency. System tested for >2 hours continuous operation without failure.

---

### 7.4 Hardware Influence on Testing

* **Sensor Precision**: Ultrasonic sensor accuracy ±1cm, IR sensor sensitive to surface reflectivity. Combined use ensures reliability in various lighting and surface conditions.
* **Latency**: Local commands execute with <200ms delay; cloud AI responses average 2–3s.
* **Battery Performance**: Robot operated for over 1.5 hours on a full charge under mixed activity (movement + AI).

